text: Thuringian is an East Central German dialect group spoken in Thuringia, southwestern Saxony-Anhalt, Hesse, and Bavaria. == Subgroups == The subgroups of Thuringian: * Central Thuringian * Northern Thuringian * Eichsfeld dialect * Eastern Thuringian * Southeastern Thuringian Other variants: * Ilm Thuringian * Northeastern Thuringian * Mansfeld dialect * Western Thuringian == References == Category:German dialects Category:Languages of Germany Category:Thuringia
title: Thuringian dialect
